Explain 'on-premises datacenter': *Who owns it? *Describe where it is located *Give one example of an opposite approach
User has to correctly name the owner (the organization itself) — score 3/10. User has to correctly describe the location (on-site / within the organization’s facilities) — score 3/10. User has to give one valid opposite example (cloud hosting or third-party datacenter) — score 4/10. Perfect score math formula: 3/10 + 3/10 + 4/10 = 10/10.
